Tech firm, APEK Group, in collaboration with PricewaterhouseCoopers (PwC) Nigeria has introduced JAVAT 365, a new digital collaboration tool to the African market to enable companies improve collaboration and communication with their employees and frontline workers. With ‘Just A Very Awesome Team All Year Round’ (JAVAT 365), organisations can have unlimited access to sharing rich media content with ease; creating and publishing news-worthy articles and surveys; creating private or public groups to foster smooth, effective collaboration among teams; instant mobile notifications to alert users of important information and video conferencing to stay connected to your remote teams and lots more. JAVAT 365 also manages users’ access and data in compliance with business standards and ensures data security by leveraging AWS infrastructures while users can send and receive emails over a secured platform with 10GB of mail storage and anti-spam filters. APEK Group’s  Co-founder/Practice Lead, Yemi Bakre described JAVAT 365 as a Software as a Service (SaaS), which offers significant saving advantage and a simpler way to collaborate with information consumers within and outside the organisation by reassessing and leveraging your existing licences. Also, Partner Technology Advisory at PwC Nigeria, Damola Yusuf, said managing a huge workforce across diverse locations could be challenging, maintaining that JAVAT 365 is a customisable, cost-effective internal collaboration tool to ease workforce communication and boost information sharing.